---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";

const meta = {
  title: "Recommended Czech Dishes - Karel's Czechia Guide",
  description: "Discover the best traditional Czech dishes and sweets you must try in Prague",
};
---

<Layout meta={meta}>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-amber-50 to-white">
    <!-- Back Navigation -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 py-4">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
        <a href="/" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700 font-medium">
          ← Back Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
          Must-Try Czech Food & Drinks
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          The essential Czech dishes and drinks every visitor should experience - what they are, why they're special, and what people really think
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sweet Dish Spotlight -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://recepty.cuketka.cz/media/recipe/main_imgs/buchticky_1_2048_80o.jpg" alt="Buchtičky s krémem" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-amber-600 bg-amber-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Sweet Dish</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Must Try</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Buchtičky s krémem</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                These fluffy steamed buns with vanilla cream sauce are the ultimate Czech comfort food. Surprisingly served as a main course, they're like little pillows of happiness. The warm vanilla cream poured over soft, sweet buns creates pure nostalgia.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "I was confused when it came as the main course instead of dessert, but wow - this is like being hugged by your grandmother. Sweet, warm, and surprisingly filling!" 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Tourist review</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Dish Spotlight -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex md:flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fd/Sv%C3%AD%C4%8Dkov%C3%A1_na_smetan%C4%9B.JPG" alt="Svíčková na smetaně" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-red-600 bg-red-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">National Dish</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Essential</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Svíčková na smetaně</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                The undisputed king of Czech cuisine. Tender beef sirloin drowning in silky cream sauce made from root vegetables, served with fluffy bread dumplings, cranberries, and a dollop of whipped cream. It's rich, it's hearty, and it's what Czechs dream about.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "This is comfort food taken to an art form. The sauce is incredibly rich and the meat just falls apart. I couldn't finish it but I didn't want to stop eating it either!" 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Food blogger</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Street Food Spotlight -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/35/Trdeln%C3%ADk_grilling.jpg" alt="Trdelník" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-amber-600 bg-amber-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Street Food</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Instagram Famous</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Trdelník</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                The spiral pastry that has taken over Prague's streets. Sweet dough wrapped around a cylinder, baked until golden, then rolled in cinnamon sugar. Technically not traditional Czech (it's from Slovakia), but it's everywhere in Prague and smells absolutely incredible.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "Yes, it's touristy. Yes, locals say it's not authentic. But honestly? It's delicious and makes for great photos. I regret nothing." 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Prague visitor</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Pub Food Spotlight -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex md:flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/SMAZENY_SYR_2020.jpg" alt="Smažený sýr" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-green-600 bg-green-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Pub Classic</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Beloved</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Smažený sýr</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Deep-fried cheese that somehow works perfectly. A thick slab of cheese, breaded and fried until golden, served with tartar sauce and potatoes or fries. It's indulgent, it's simple, and it's exactly what you want after a few beers.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "I was skeptical about fried cheese as a main course, but this was actually amazing. Crispy outside, melty inside, pure comfort food!" 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Vegetarian tourist</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Traditional Trilogy -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://live.staticflickr.com/3908/14482291555_b8a2d733ff_b.jpg" alt="Vepřo knedlo zelo" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-orange-600 bg-orange-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Classic Trio</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Traditional</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Vepřo knedlo zelo</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                The holy trinity of Czech cuisine: roasted pork, bread dumplings, and sauerkraut. It's hearty, satisfying, and represents everything Czech food stands for. Each component perfectly balances the others.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "This is what my Czech grandmother would have made if I had one. So traditional and filling - I couldn't move for an hour!" 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Food enthusiast</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Hearty Soup -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex md:flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/ea/S%C3%A4chsische_Kartoffelsuppe%2C_Alte_Apotheke%2C_Altk%C3%B6tzschenbroda.jpg" alt="Bramboračka" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-yellow-600 bg-yellow-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Comfort Soup</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Winter Favorite</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Bramboračka</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                The ultimate comfort soup made with potatoes, mushrooms, and marjoram. Thick, creamy, and warming - perfect for Prague's cold winters. Often served with crusty bread and sometimes a sausage.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "Like a warm hug in a bowl. Perfect after walking around Prague in the cold!" 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Winter visitor</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Festive Dish -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/87/Kachna_pe%C4%8Den%C3%A1_s_jablky%2C_knedl%C3%ADk_a_zel%C3%AD_-_detail_20.jpg" alt="Kachna" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-purple-600 bg-purple-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Special Occasion</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Festive</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Kachna</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Roasted duck with apples, bread dumplings, and red cabbage. This is Czech dining at its most elegant - crispy skin, tender meat, and the sweet-tart combination of apples and cabbage. Often served at Christmas and special celebrations.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "Absolutely incredible! The duck was perfectly cooked and the apple-cabbage combo was a revelation." 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Fine dining lover</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Hearty Goulash -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex md:flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://live.staticflickr.com/2432/3647615216_1f95e4dd3c_b.jpg" alt="Guláš" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-red-600 bg-red-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Hearty Stew</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Warming</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Guláš</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Rich beef stew with onions, paprika, and tender chunks of meat, served with bread dumplings. It's the kind of dish that sticks to your ribs and warms you from the inside. Perfect pub food that pairs beautifully with Czech beer.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "So much more complex than I expected! The paprika gives it this amazing depth of flavor." 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Stew enthusiast</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Street Snack -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c8/Bramboracky.jpg" alt="Bramborák" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-green-600 bg-green-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Street Snack</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Crispy</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Bramborák</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Crispy potato pancakes that are the perfect street food or pub snack. Made with grated potatoes, garlic, and marjoram, then fried until golden. Often served with sour cream or applesauce. Simple but absolutely addictive.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "Like the best hash browns you've ever had but somehow even better. I kept ordering more!" 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Street food fan</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Bite -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex md:flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <img src="https://cdn.myshoptet.com/usr/www.sistersbistro.cz/user/documents/upload/2.jpg" alt="Chlebíčky" class="w-full h-64 md:h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 bg-blue-100 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Quick Lunch</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Artful</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Chlebíčky</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Open-faced sandwiches that are like edible art pieces. Each one is carefully constructed with various meats, vegetables, and spreads on quality bread. Perfect for a quick lunch that's both beautiful and delicious.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
                  "They're almost too pretty to eat! But so fresh and tasty - way better than regular sandwiches." 
                  <span class="font-medium">- Lunch visitor</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Drinks Section -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-red-600">Essential Czech Drinks</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- Pilsner Urquell -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
            <img src="https://live.staticflickr.com/5087/5293033730_6cf84b756f_b.jpg" alt="Pilsner Urquell" class="w-full h-48 object-cover">
            <div class="p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Pilsner Urquell</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">The original pilsner beer, invented in 1842 in Plzen. Crisp, hoppy, and served unpasteurized in Prague - the way beer should taste.</p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs text-gray-600 italic">
                "Finally understood what beer is supposed to taste like!" - Beer tourist
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Kozel -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/83/Kozelek.jpg" alt="Velkopopovický Kozel" class="w-full h-48 object-cover">
            <div class="p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Velkopopovický Kozel</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">The goat beer! Smooth, malty, and less hoppy than Pilsner. Perfect for those who find other Czech beers too bitter.</p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs text-gray-600 italic">
                "Smoother than expected, and I love the goat logo everywhere!" - Pub crawler
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Kofola -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/85/Sklenice_Kofola.jpg" alt="Kofola" class="w-full h-48 object-cover">
            <div class="p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Kofola</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">The Czech Coca-Cola that predates it! Made with natural caffeine from coffee beans, less sweet, and surprisingly herbal. A true taste of Czech nostalgia.</p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs text-gray-600 italic">
                "It tastes like cola's more sophisticated European cousin." - Curious traveler
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>